This paper focuses on analysing Twitter data related to the 2016 US presidential election using NLP methods. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL) as it involves natural language processing techniques. It also involves social media analysis, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also uses supervised topic modelling, which can be categorised under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper involves sentiment analysis, which can be categorised under the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it involves analysing the attitude of tweets. Finally, the paper also involves analysing patterns in the data, which can be categorised under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
